Building The Model|TASK 2

Build a classification model labeling houses as being built “before 1980” or “during or after 1980”. Your goal is to reach or exceed 90% accuracy. Explain your final model choice (algorithm, tuning parameters, etc) and describe what other models you tried.

I will now build the model and see how accurate it will be

Read and format data 
# Include and execute your code here

X_pred = dwellings_ml.drop(dwellings_ml.filter(regex = 'before1980|yrbuilt|parcel|smonth|syear').columns, axis = 1)
y_pred = dwellings_ml.filter(regex = "before1980")
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(
    X_pred, y_pred, test_size = .34, random_state = 76)
Show the code 
clf = tree.DecisionTreeClassifier()
clf = clf.fit(X_train, y_train)
y_pred = clf.predict(X_test)
y_probs = clf.predict_proba(X_test)

print(metrics.classification_report(y_pred, y_test))
              precision    recall  f1-score   support

Justifying My Choices of Columns|Task 3

Justify your classification model by discussing the most important features selected by your model. This discussion should include a chart and a description of the features.

I think that number of baths was one of the most important columns to tell when a house was built, because like in the graph earlier, it shows that there are quite a spike in houses with more than 1 - 2 baths after 1980. This, in turn, helps the model decide when a house was built before or after 1980.

Quality Report|TASK 4

Describe the quality of your classification model using 2-3 different evaluation metrics. You also need to explain how to interpret each of the evaluation metrics you use.

I think that my classification model was very profecient in deciding which houses were built before 1980 due to the metric scores that it got. It got an 89% in precision, an 86% in recall and a 91% in accuracy. This all means that it, generally speaking, recieved a grade at 90 or above on all metrics. This is a trustworthy model! I think that precision is the most important metric of all of the 3 because it shows that it can pin point, rather than jut guess “built after 1980” every time.
